# GitSpec Core Rules

This project uses GitSpec for repo-native project management. Read `AGENTS.md` at the
project root for the full contract.

## Key Conventions

- Specs live in `docs/specs/SPEC-{domain}-{number}.md` with YAML frontmatter
- Stories live in `docs/stories/STORY-{number}.md` with YAML frontmatter
- Status vocabulary: {{STATUS_VALUES}}
- feat/fix commits require `Story:` or `Spec:` trailers
- Working notes go in `docs/notes/{contributor}/{YYYY-MM-DD}.md`
- Never hand-edit `.ledger/changes.json`
- Before PR: distill raw notes into an ADR in `docs/decisions/`

## Before Implementing

1. Check `docs/specs/` for relevant requirements
2. Check `docs/stories/` for the target story and its acceptance criteria
3. If no story exists for the work, create one first

## Commit Format

```
type(scope): description

Story: STORY-NNN
Spec: SPEC-XXX-NNN
```

Types: feat, fix, perf, refactor, docs, test, chore, style, ci
